 oy oz pa oh pb pc pd pe bg" data-selectable-paragraph=3D"">What Will You B=
uild?</h3><p id=3D"555a" class=3D"pw-post-body-paragraph nq nr ho ns b im p=
f nu nv ip pg nx ny nz ph ob oc od pi of og oh pj oj ok ol hh bg" data-sele=
ctable-paragraph=3D"">At this point you should have a working development e=
nvironment, similar to what Ariella had. She spent a few days learning ARM =
assembly and came up with a simple project she wanted to code: a simple Sev=
en-Boom game. Seven-boom is an Israeli variation of Fizz Buzz. Players take=
 turns counting incrementally, and whenever a number is divisible by seven =
or contains the digit 7, they need to say =E2=80=9CBoom=E2=80=9D.</p><p id=
=3D"10f1" class=3D"pw-post-body-paragraph nq nr ho ns b im nt nu nv ip nw n=
x ny nz oa ob oc od oe of og oh oi oj ok ol hh bg" data-selectable-paragrap=
h=3D"">Completing this game was quite a challenge as she had to write a met=
hod that would print numbers to screen, one digit at a time =E2=80=94 as th=
e idea was to write everything from scratch using Assembly code and without=
 calling any standard C library functions. But after a few days of tinkerin=
g and hard work she did it!</p><p id=3D"7c59" class=3D"pw-post-body-paragra=
ph nq nr ho ns b im nt nu nv ip nw nx ny nz oa ob oc od oe of og oh oi oj o=
k ol hh bg" data-selectable-paragraph=3D"">You can find <a class=3D"z pn" h=
ref=3D"https://gist.github.com/urish/4151e0acdc315c6ee548ba6e9ee3a66e" rel=
=3D"noopener ugc nofollow" target=3D"_blank">her first Android program, the=
 7-boom, here</a>. Some of the identifiers in the code are actually hebrew =
words (like <code class=3D"db px py pz qa b">_sifra_ahrona</code>, which me=
ans =E2=80=9CLast digits=E2=80=9D =E2=80=94 she found it more fun this way,=
 and I found it cute).</p><p id=3D"b35e" class=3D"pw-post-body-paragraph nq=
 nr ho ns b im nt nu nv ip nw nx ny nz oa ob oc od oe of og oh oi oj ok ol =
hh bg" data-selectable-paragraph=3D"">Writing assembly code for your Androi=
d device is a great way to familiarize yourself with the ARM architecture, =
and get a better understanding of the inner-workings of a device you use on=
 a daily basis.</p><p id=3D"61f1" class=3D"pw-post-body-paragraph nq nr ho =
ns b im nt nu nv ip nw nx ny nz oa ob oc od oe of og oh oi oj ok ol hh bg" =
data-selectable-paragraph=3D"">I challenge you to go ahead and write a smal=
l assembly program for your Android phone. It could be a simple <a class=3D=
"z pn" href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Bulls_and_Cows" rel=3D"noopene=
r ugc nofollow" target=3D"_blank">Bulls and Cows game</a>, a <a class=3D"z =
pn" href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Hangman_(game)" rel=3D"noopener u=
gc nofollow" target=3D"_blank">hangman</a> clone, or whatever you like =E2=
=80=94 when you finish, please share the code with me, I=E2=80=99d love to =
see how creative you can get!</p></div></div></div><div class=3D"v cf qx qy=
 qz ra" role=3D"separator"><span class=3D"rb bu bi rc rd re"></span><span c=
lass=3D"rb bu bi rc rd re"></span><span class=3D"rb bu bi rc rd"></span></d=
